French, Italians Among Most Gloomy About Economy, FT Reports

-- B y   R a c h e l   G r a h a m
-- 
2011-07-23T09:36:28Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-23/french-italians-among-most-gloomy-about-economy-ft-reports.html
French and Italian consumers are
among the most pessimistic about their economies, the Financial
Times reported, citing an Ipsos-Mori poll of 24 countries.  The U.K. ranked as sixth most pessimistic, with only one in
eight rating the economy as “good,” the newspaper said.  Japan ,
 Hungary  and  Spain  also ranked among the most gloomy, the
Financial Times added.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Rachel Graham in London 
